name: Crystal Palace
summary: Crystal Palace defeated Stockport County 1-0 in the FA Cup's third round, with Eberechi Eze scoring the game-winning goal. Meanwhile, plans for the Crystal Palace Main Stand redevelopment continue, while the club is nearing a £150 million share deal with a Saudi-backed group. Tragically, the search for missing Crystal Palace FC charity workers in Italy has led to the discovery of a body. Despite a sickness bug affecting the squad before the game, Crystal Palace emerged victorious with Eze's early strike. In other news, a Championship club is set to receive a club-record fee from Crystal Palace for an England U20 star.
